<doc>
  <member name="DML_CONVOLUTION_DIRECTION">
    <summary>
      <para>Defines constants that specify a direction for the DirectML convolution operator (as described by the <see cref="DML_CONVOLUTION_OPERATOR_DESC" /> structure).</para>
    </summary>
    <seealso cref="DML_CONVOLUTION_OPERATOR_DESC" />
  </member>
  <member name="DML_CONVOLUTION_DIRECTION.DML_CONVOLUTION_DIRECTION_FORWARD">
    <summary>
      <para>Indicates a forward convolution.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="DML_CONVOLUTION_DIRECTION.DML_CONVOLUTION_DIRECTION_BACKWARD">
    <summary>
      <para>Indicates a backward convolution. Backward convolution is also known as <i>transposed</i> convolution.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>